The paper deals with generating adversarial examples to deceive deep learning models used for malware detection. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as well as machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves modifying executable files, which could fall under software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper uses convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV), although this is less likely to be the primary category given the focus on malware detection.
